726879f-b.title: Queens: Hollis Avenue - 99th Avenue
726879f-b.text:
Hollis Ave., east side, between Ninety-ninth Ave. (left, not
shown) and One Hundredth Ave., showing in a set of two views the
D. Eetchum residence located on a triangular plot of ground bounded
in addition to the aforementioned streets by 193rd Street. It is now
known as the Hollis Nurseries. From 1860 to 1891 the first mentioned
person was the owner of this property. View No. 2 is taken from Nine-
ty Fourth Ave., viewing S.W.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726883f-a.title: Queens: Hollis Avenue - Farmers Boulevard
726883f-a.text:
Hollis Ave. (0ld Country Road), south side, west of Farmers
Boulevard, showing the S. Spragg house of 186O which was demolished
in 1925. District School No. 2 is at the left. All that is seen of
it is the entrance into the building.
1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726878f-a.title: Queens: Hollis Avenue - 99th Avenue
726878f-a.text:
Hollis Ave., east side, between Ninety-minth and One Hundredth
Aves., showing the David Netcham house of 1891. One Gilkinson main-
tained a florist establishment here in 1918.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
